# CrokyScopy Project Rules

## Core Technologies
- **JUCE 8**: C++ framework for audio processing and GUI.
- **CMake**: Build system.
- **Target**: VST3 Plugin (Release / x64).

## Project Structure
- `Source/`: All C++ source files.
- `ScopeBuffer.h`: High-performance, lock-free oscilloscope buffer.
- `HUDWindow.h/cpp`: Win32-specific "HUD" overlay logic (Topmost, Layered, Click-through).
- `ScopeComponent.h/cpp`: Waveform rendering and mouse interaction.

## HUD Interaction Rules
- **Move**: Left-click & drag anywhere on the HUD (in Edit Mode).
- **Resize**: Right-click & drag anywhere on the HUD (in Edit Mode).
-lity**: Toggle `WS_EX_TRANSPARENT` in `HUDWindow::setWindowAttributes` to switch between "Interactive" and "Click-through".
 **Control**: All interactions MUST be through the whole-window mouse handlers in `ScopeComponent`, NOT the parent `HUDWindow`.
- **Visibi
## Sync Logic
- **Beat-Sync**: Uses DAW PPQ. 2/4/8/16 beat cycles.
- **Free-Run**: Uses `std::fmod` on a time-based counter (10ms - 5s).
- **Transport Sync**: If enabled, only updates when `getPlayHead()->getPosition()->getIsPlaying()` is true.

## Visual Standards
- **Color**: Waveform color mapped from the `hue` parameter (HSV).
- **Opacity**: `opacity` parameter ONLY affects the background/grid, never the line itself.
- **Accuracy**: Always render from the midpoint of the `ScopeBuffer` bins to avoid visual DC offsets.
- **Seams**: Maintain "Invisible Seams" in Paging mode by only starting a new sub-path at the write-index.

## Communication Rules
- **Conciseness**: Keep all responses as short and direct as possible.
- **No Token Bloat**: Do not provide overly long explanations or repetitive summaries.
- **Direct Answer**: Just answer the question directly, without unnecessary preamble.
- **Action over words**: Perform tasks and report only essential information or errors.
